7. now, go to node-1 -> bin -> start elasticsearch.bat file
8. copy the enrollment token and password, use them in kibana ui
9. now create an index, a shard and replica will be created.
10. the replica shard will be unassigned and the health of index, shard, cluster will be yellow (at risk)
11. so now to configure other nodes to join this cluster
	* on this node:
		create an enrollment token with 'bin/elasticsearch-create-enrollment-token -s node'
	* on the node-2:
		open cmd in bin directory path, and execute 'elasticsearch.bat --enrollment-token <token>'
		and start the bat file
12. now since the cluster has two nodes, node-1 and node-2. the replica shard will be assigned to node-2
13. and we see the green status.
14. will not add node-3 to this cluster. because if we add then every time we start the cluster we need to make
    sure atleast 2/3 nodes are started.

